<hl>
<seg id=1> The American Federal Reserve Board might further reduce the rate of interest. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Reuters, Washington Vice Chairman of the American Federal Reserve Board Alan Blinder warned that the global financial storm would slow down a lot the American economy, and he hinted that America might have to reduce the rate of interest to avoid the economic recession. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> Alan Blinder said during his interview that he didn't think that the American economy would collapse, but he warned that a decline in export value and employment meant that the economy slowed down a lot. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> The Federal Reserve Board had reduced the rate twice in the past 6 weeks to avoid the effect of the most serious financial storm in the last half century to the American economy. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> The Federal Reserve Board would hold a meeting on 17 November to discuss the issue. </seg>
<seg id=6> It's guessed that the board would decide to reduce the rate again to maintain the stability of the economy. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> The American economy only increased by 3.3% for the third quarter, and it's lower than the first quarter, which was 5.5%. </seg>
<seg id=8> It's estimated that the economy in the following months would slow down. </seg>
<seg id=9> It's because a decline in American exports to Asia affected the investment and production of the American manufacturing industry. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> Alan Blinder pointed out that the high pressure of American finance in recent weeks was slightly subsiding. </seg>
<seg id=11> But he warned that the retrenchment of loan still existed. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=12> Alan Blinder thought that the world economy still had not got rid of the crisis. </seg>
<seg id=13> Asian recovery was still at the early stage. </seg>
<seg id=14> The second strongest economic country Japan had not recovered yet, but the Russian economy was "still bad". </seg>
</p>
